Interface Strategy

All Known Implementing Classes:
AnalysisA, AnalysisB, AnalysisC, AnalysisD, AnalysisE, AnalysisF, AnalysisG, AnalysisH
public interface Strategy
This interface is used to define an abstraction for the strategy used to compute the analysis. It has one method that will be overridden by all the classes that implement it.
Version:
1.0.0
Author:
Matthew Bertuzzi.
See Also:
AnalysisMap

  • Method Details

    • doAnalysis

      boolean doAnalysis​(java.lang.String country, int givenStartyear, int givenEndYear, Model modelRef)
      This function is overridden to implement the specific strategy used for the various types of analysis being offered by the application.
      Parameters:
      country - The user chosen country for analysis.
      givenStartyear - The user chosen start year for analysis.
      givenEndYear - The user chosen end year for analysis.
      modelRef - A reference to the model used to store data.
      Returns:
      True if the analysis was completed successfully, false otherwise.
